{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>PatriciaTree.HomogeneousValue</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"patricia-tree","href":"../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"PatriciaTree","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"HomogeneousValue","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>Default implementation of <a href=\"../module-type-HETEROGENEOUS_VALUE/index.html\"><code>HETEROGENEOUS_VALUE</code></a>, to use when the type of the value in a heterogeneous map does not depend on the type of the key, only on the type of the map.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <span>('a, 'map) t</span></span><span> = <span class=\"type-var\">'map</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>The type of values. A <code>'map map</code> maps <code>'key key</code> to <code>('key, 'map) value</code>. Can be mutable if desired, unless it is being used in <a href=\"../index.html#hash_consed\" title=\"hash_consed\">Hash-consed maps and sets</a>.</p></div></div>"}